OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy at first in the morning
OL,6,Fwith a few showery outbreaks of rain.
OL,7,FTurning drier through the day with
OL,8,Fincreasing amounts of sunshine.
OL,9,FFeeling much fresher than recent days.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FDry and sunny into the
OL,12,Fevening, with clear spells overnight,
OL,13,Fcloud increasing from the west towards
OL,14,Fdawn. Much cooler than recent nights.
OL,15,
OL,16,CMonday:FA bright or sunny start,
OL,17,Fparticularly across the east of the
OL,18,Fregion. Skies turning hazy, leading to
OL,19,Fbright spells during the afternoon.
OL,20,FTemperatures close to the late June
OL,21,Faverage.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
